import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import { Playground } from 'docz'
import Button from './index'

export default class MDXContent extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props)
    this.layout = null
  }
  render() {
    const { components, ...props } = this.props

    return <MDXTag
             name="wrapper"
             
             components={components}>
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"button"}}>{`Button`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"default"}}>{`Default`}</MDXTag>
<Playground __codesandbox={`undefined`} __position={0} __code={`<Button>Hello</Button>`} __scope={{props: this ? this.props : props,Button}}>
  <Button>Hello</Button>
</Playground>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"outlined"}}>{`Outlined`}</MDXTag>
<Playground __codesandbox={`undefined`} __position={1} __code={`<Button type="outlined">Hello</Button>`} __scope={{props: this ? this.props : props,Button}}>
  <Button type="outlined">Hello</Button>
</Playground>
           </MDXTag>
  }
}
